article.headline: BYU 92, Weber St. 62
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Lee Cummard shot 12-of-13 from the field for 30 points in BYU's 92-62 win over Weber State on Wednesday night. Jimmer Fredette added 18 points, including four 3-pointers, while Jonathan Tavernari finished with 11 points for BYU (7-0). The Cougars, who went 11-of-25 from 3-point range, went into the half ahead 46-39. Back-to-back baskets by James Anderson gave BYU its biggest lead of the night, 92-60, with 1:15 left in the game. The 30-point deficit was the worst loss for WSU at home against BYU in school history. Kyle Bullinger led the Wildcats (2-4) with a career-high 16 points, all of them coming in the first half. Steve Panos added 12 points, and Daviin Davis finished with 10.
